OL,3,CNHS whistleblowing: Health workers ask
OL,4,Cto join Lucy Letby inquiry
OL,6,F"They are requesting the opportunity
OL,7,Fto be given a platform at an inquiry
OL,8,Fof huge national importance to speak
OL,9,Fcollectively as a voice of experience.
OL,11,F"They are experts in their fields who
OL,12,Fhave seen things go wrong first-hand.
OL,14,F"Since the Francis Report in 2015,
OL,15,Ffollowing the Mid Staffordshire NHS
OL,16,FFoundation Trust Public Inquiry, there
OL,17,Fhas been a series of investigations
OL,18,Finto NHS trusts around patient safety
OL,19,Fwhere it has been revealed NHS staff
OL,20,Fhave either been too scared to speak
OL,21,Fup or punished for speaking up.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUvD@AOU
