OL,3,CNHS whistleblowing: Health workers ask
OL,4,Cto join Lucy Letby inquiry
OL,6,F"Lessons have clearly not been learned
OL,7,Fand we feel it is imperative that this
OL,8,Fgroup be involved in the Thirlwall
OL,9,FInquiry, particularly to help examine
OL,10,Fwhether suspicions could have been
OL,11,Fraised earlier, whether Letby should
OL,12,Fhave been suspended earlier, and how
OL,13,Fthe management responded to concerns
OL,14,Fraised about her.
OL,16,F"The evidence of this group relating
OL,17,Fto how whistleblowers are treated, not
OL,18,Fjust at one trust, but across the UK,
OL,19,Fis of huge significance."
